id: pm-xaib
title: "GH-363: Windows nightly (Node 24) red — runtime-loader colon-path + telemetry detached-spawn unhandled error + npm-install regression"
description: "Nightly Validation windows-latest/Node24 (GH-363, run 28155165798) fails with THREE deterministic symptoms after the 2026-06-24 matrix bump from Node 20 to Node 24 (commit be5be995): (1) tests/unit/packages/runtime-loaders.spec.ts 'continues when Node reports a forward-slashed missing runtime path' (pm-beads + pm-todos) raised ENOENT because the coverage fixture synthesized a literal 'C:\\pm\\project' directory segment — the colon is reserved on Windows so mkdir fails; (2) tests/integration/cli.integration.spec.ts 'installs runtime dependencies for packed npm package extensions' returned install code 1 (npm.cmd shell-spawn / tar / hosted-SDK junction class, Windows-only); (3) the long-standing teardown 'Worker forks emitted error / Worker exited unexpectedly' (GH-348 / pm-2kkl) whose root cause is the telemetry detached flush spawn in src/core/telemetry/runtime.ts missing a child.on('error') handler — an async spawn failure becomes an unhandled error that crashes the vitest worker (the sibling search background-refresh spawn already had this guard). Fix bundle: platform-aware runtime-loader fixture, child.on('error') gate-release on the telemetry spawn mirroring background-refresh, spawn-mocked telemetry test (no real network-touching orphan child), install-failure diagnostics, and expanded per-PR windows-regression Node 24 guards covering all three classes."
type: Issue
status: in_progress
priority: 1
tags[7]: "area:ci","area:telemetry","area:tests",cross-platform,flake,node24,windows
