comments[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-25T09:26:43.003Z",claude-code-agent,"PR #365 opened: https://github.com/unbraind/pm-cli/pull/365 — fix bundle for the Windows nightly Node 24 red (runtime-loader colon-path fixture, telemetry detached-spawn child.on(\"error\") hardening + spawn-mocked test, install diagnostics, expanded windows-regression Node 24 guards). Awaiting CI (windows-regression Node 24 is the Windows oracle) + AI bot reviews.\n"
  "2026-06-25T09:47:29.528Z",claude-code-agent,"Windows-regression (Node 24) on PR #365 surfaced the real integration failure via the new diagnostic: `npm pack` received `pm-test-...@file:///C:/Users/RUNNER%7E1/...` and opened the literal `RUNNER%7E1` path -> ENOENT. Root cause: pathToFileURL percent-encodes the Windows 8.3 `~` short name (and spaces -> %20), and pm passed that encoded file URL straight to npm, which opens it literally. This is a real cross-platform bug — reproduced on Linux with a space-containing path. Fix: resolveNpmPackSpec + normalizeNpmLocalFileAliasSpec now hand npm pack a NATIVE decoded filesystem path (via fileURLToPath) instead of a percent-encoded file URL, and decode file:///abs alias targets (previously bailed on the `//` prefix), while leaving file://host/share UNC specs untouched. Verified end-to-end on Linux: `pm install npm:file:///…/pm%20install%20space…/my%20pkg` now succeeds (was ENOENT). 5096 tests, 100/100/100/100 coverage.\n"
body: ""
